        fullName: 'Avariel',
        baseRaceId: 3,
        baseRaceTypeId: 1743923279,
        description:
          '<p>Elves are a magical people of otherworldly grace, living in the world but not entirely part of it.</p>\r\n<p class="characters-statblock" style="font-family: Roboto Condensed;"><strong>Racial Traits</strong><br />+2 Dexterity, Darkvision, Keen Senses, Fey Ancestry, Trance</p><p>The Avariels are elves with direct lineage to celestial beings. They typically have fair skin, ranging from sunkissed creamy to a pale moonlight like color. Their eyes can reflect any color, and typically change depending on their mood. Many Avariel have <span class="ILfuVd"><span class="hgKElc">Heterochromia iridium</span></span>, a condition where their eyes are actually two different colors. The most unique feature of these elves though is how their divine heritage manifests. They are blessed with great feathery wings, capable of great flight. The wings themselves can be almost any color, from the speckled white with black marks of a snow owl, to the mottled brown of an eagle, to the dark black of a raven.<br><br> The wings themselves are strong, and the Avariel are able to fly even when carrying heavy loads. However, the large wingspan means they cant fly if they cant spread their wings, so Avariel avoid tight spaces. This has resulted in a culture designed to living in wide open spaces, with the winged elves living in tall trees or atop large mountains or plateaus.&nbsp; Angelic elves weave clothes in elegant patterns with slots designed for their wings, and take great pride in colorful outfits of cloth or silk. <br><br>Avariel warriors are able to wear their armor unhindered by the weight, flying with ease even in full plated armor. The winged elves design their armor with their wings in mind, some even having armor that covers the forelimbs for extra protection. The feathers of an Avariel are incredibly strong, more durable than most normal bird feathers. This results in an unfortunate habit of game hunters to chase down and slay Avariel\'s caught alone. Their wings are a great prize, being worth a pretty bit of coin to the right buyers.<br><br>Because of their hunting, Avariel are a rather private race, avoiding contact with others to the exception of other elves that might set up in the trees below them. Avariel elves are almost universally respected by normal elves (to the exception of Drow), due to their direct connection to elvish Gods and Goddesses, and their divine servants. <br><br>Avariel that choose the adventuring life will find many people see them as inspiring beacons, some even thinking them Angels sent by the heavens. The rare Avariel who chooses to commit themselves to a darker purpose in life find themselves seen as an angel of death, a symbol to be feared. Such corruption of their divine blood can stain their body alongside their soul, turning their wings ashy grey or black as night. Fear the shadow of a winged elf, for they bring fierce strength from the skies above.</p>',
